# BaseAnchor

`TxBaseAnchor` is the low-level positioning primitive for floating content. It only handles geometry, open/close state, and lifecycle hooks. Panel visuals are intentionally left to consumer components such as `TxCard`, `TxPopover`, or custom content.

Use `#reference` for the trigger area and `#content` for the floating layer. This split keeps behavior and rendering responsibilities clear.

## Basic Usage

### BaseAnchor
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BaseAnchorBasicDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const open = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxBaseAnchor v-model="open" placement="bottom-start" :offset="10">
      <template #reference>
        <TxButton @click="open = !open">Click</TxButton>
      </template>

      <template #content>
        <TxCard shadow="soft" :radius="14" :padding="12" style="width: 240px;">
          Basic floating panel powered by anchor positioning and v-model control.
        </TxCard>
      </template>
    </TxBaseAnchor>
  </template>
---
:::

## Arrow Rendering

When `show-arrow` is enabled, arrow geometry is provided through `#content` slot props (`arrowRef`, `arrowStyle`, `arrowSide`).

### Arrow
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BaseAnchorSplitLineDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const open = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxBaseAnchor v-model="open" placement="bottom-start" :offset="12" :show-arrow="true" :arrow-size="10">
      <template #reference>
        <TxButton @click="open = !open">Arrow</TxButton>
      </template>

      <template #content="{ arrowRef, arrowStyle, arrowSide }">
        <div :ref="arrowRef" :style="arrowStyle" :data-side="arrowSide" class="anchor-arrow" />
        <TxCard shadow="soft" :radius="14" :padding="12" style="width: 260px;">
          Render the directional arrow with slot props from the anchor core.
        </TxCard>
      </template>
    </TxBaseAnchor>
  </template>
---
:::

## Placement

Floating UI placement is passed through directly, including edge variants such as `bottom-start` and `right-end`.

### Placement Directions
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BaseAnchorPlacementDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const openBottom = ref(false)
  const openTop = ref(false)
  const openLeft = ref(false)
  const openRight = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxBaseAnchor v-model="openBottom" placement="bottom">
      <template #reference>
        <TxButton @click="openBottom = !openBottom">Bottom</TxButton>
      </template>
      <template #content>
        <TxCard shadow="soft" :radius="12" :padding="10" style="width: 180px;">bottom</TxCard>
      </template>
    </TxBaseAnchor>
  </template>
---
:::

## Auto Resize

Enable `auto-resize` to re-measure floating bounds whenever content layout changes.

### Auto Resize
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BaseAnchorCustomEaseDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const open = ref(false)
  const expanded = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxBaseAnchor
      v-model="open"
      placement="bottom-start"
      :auto-resize="true"
      :min-width="220"
      :max-width="340"
      :max-height="320"
    >
      <template #reference>
        <TxButton @click="open = !open">Auto Resize</TxButton>
      </template>

      <template #content>
        <TxCard shadow="soft" :radius="14" :padding="12">
          <TxButton size="sm" variant="ghost" @click="expanded = !expanded">Expand details</TxButton>
          <div v-if="expanded">The floating panel recomputes its size when content changes.</div>
        </TxCard>
      </template>
    </TxBaseAnchor>
  </template>
---
:::

## API

### TxBaseAnchor Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `modelValue` | `boolean` | `false` | Open state (v-model). |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disable interaction. |
| `placement` | `BaseAnchorPlacement` | `'bottom-start'` | Floating placement. |
| `offset` | `number` | `8` | Gap from reference element (px). |
| `width` | `number` | `0` | Fixed width when greater than 0. |
| `minWidth` | `number` | `0` | Minimum floating width (px). |
| `maxWidth` | `number` | `360` | Maximum floating width (px). |
| `maxHeight` | `number` | `420` | Maximum floating height (px). |
| `matchReferenceWidth` | `boolean` | `false` | Force floating width to reference width when `width` is 0. |
| `referenceFullWidth` | `boolean` | `false` | Stretch reference container to full width. |
| `motion` | `'fade' \| 'split'` | `'split'` | Motion style for enter/leave transition. |
| `autoResize` | `boolean` | `false` | Enable automatic resize sync via `TxAutoSizer`. |
| `autoResizeWidth` | `boolean` | `true` | Auto-resize width axis. |
| `autoResizeHeight` | `boolean` | `true` | Auto-resize height axis. |
| `closeOnClickOutside` | `boolean` | `true` | Close when clicking outside. |
| `closeOnEsc` | `boolean` | `true` | Close on Escape key. |
| `transition` | `string` | `'tx-base-anchor'` | Vue transition name applied to floating layer. Pass empty string to disable. |
| `referenceAs` | `string` | `'span'` | Tag used by reference wrapper. |
| `floatingAs` | `string` | `'div'` | Tag used by floating wrapper. |
| `referenceProps` | `Record<string, any>` | `undefined` | Extra props bound to reference wrapper. |
| `floatingProps` | `Record<string, any>` | `undefined` | Extra props bound to floating wrapper. |
| `referenceClass` | `string \| string[] \| Record<string, boolean>` | `undefined` | Class override for reference wrapper. |
| `floatingClass` | `string \| string[] \| Record<string, boolean>` | `undefined` | Class override for floating wrapper. |
| `floatingStyle` | `StyleValue` | `undefined` | Inline style override for floating wrapper. |
| `showArrow` | `boolean` | `false` | Enable arrow middleware output. |
| `arrowSize` | `number` | `12` | Logical arrow size used for offset calculations. |
| `virtualRef` | `BaseAnchorVirtualRef` | `undefined` | Virtual reference object for non-DOM triggers. |
| `onBeforeEnter` | `(el: Element) => void` | `undefined` | Hook called before enter transition starts. |

### Events

| Event | Params | Description |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `update:modelValue` | `boolean` | v-model state sync. |
| `open` | - | Fired when state switches to open. |
| `close` | - | Fired when state switches to closed. |
| `before-enter` | `Element` | Fired before enter transition. |

### Slots

| Slot | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `reference` | Trigger content rendered inside the reference wrapper. |
| `content` | Floating content area. |

`content` slot props:

| Prop | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `arrowStyle` | `Record<string, string>` | Computed arrow style from Floating UI middleware. |
| `arrowSide` | `string` | Final side (`top`/`right`/`bottom`/`left`) after flip/shift. |
| `arrowRef` | `Ref<HTMLElement \| null>` | Arrow element ref used by middleware. |
| `arrowData` | `any` | Raw arrow middleware data. |

### Exposed Methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `open()` | Open the floating panel. |
| `close()` | Close the floating panel. |
| `toggle()` | Toggle panel state. |
| `update()` | Force a position recomputation. |

### Exposed Refs

| Ref | Description |
|-----|-------------|
| `referenceRef` | Reference wrapper element ref. |
| `floatingRef` | Floating wrapper element ref. |
